President Trump delivered remarks at a Hanukkah reception in the East Room of the White House. He thanked the attendees and expressed his appreciation for the Jewish faith and the contributions of the Jewish community to the United States. He also praised his administration's actions in support of Israel, including recognizing Jerusalem as the capital and signing an executive order to combat anti-Semitism. The President highlighted the importance of the FIRST STEP Act, a criminal justice reform bill, and recognized individuals who have been impacted by it. The event concluded with the lighting of the menorah.